0.name: git_blob_lookup
0.description:
Lookup a blob object from a repository.
 The generated blob object is owned by the revision
 repo and shall not be freed by the user.

2.description:
Fill a blob with the contents inside

5.description: Get the size in bytes of the contents of a blob

6.name: git_blob_writefile
6.description:
Read a file from the working folder of a repository

 if such doesn't exist yet.

81.name: GIT_SORT_NONE
81.description: Sort the repository contents in no particular ordering; this sorting is arbitrary, implementation-specific and subject to change at any time. This is the default sorting for new walkers.

82.name: GIT_SORT_TOPOLOGICAL
82.description: Sort the repository contents in topological order (parents before children); this sorting mode can be combined with time sorting.

83.name: GIT_SORT_TIME
83.description: Sort the repository contents by commit time; this sorting mode can be combined with topological sorting.

84.name: GIT_SORT_REVERSE
84.description: Iterate through the repository contents in reverse order; this sorting mode can be combined with any of the above.

85.description: Allocate a new revision walker to iterate through a repo.

86.description: Reset the walking machinery for reuse.

87.name: git_revwalk_push
87.description:
Mark a commit to start traversal from.
 The commit object must belong to the repo which is being walked through.

88.name: git_revwalk_hide
88.description: Mark a commit (and its ancestors) uninteresting for the output.

89.name: git_revwalk_next
89.description: Get the next commit from the revision traversal.

90.name: git_revwalk_sorting
90.description:
Change the sorting mode when iterating through the
 repository's contents.
 Changing the sorting mode resets the walker.

92.name: git_revwalk_repository
92.description:
Return the repository on which this walker
 is operating.
